blackvue-tools

Started in 2026 by Christer R (sssreh).

The project originated from a Bash script used to synchronize
recordings from a BlackVue DR900S installed in a vehicle named
Kirby.

Its goal is to create an open, privacy-focused, cross-platform
framework for understanding, documenting, and automating dashcams.

The project is designed to be vendor-neutral at its core, with
manufacturer-specific adapters beginning with BlackVue.

We welcome everyone—from developers and reverse engineers to
hardware testers and documentation contributors.